\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Herbaceous or suffruticose perennials, with more or less elongated branches bearing small, spirally arranged leaves which are without veins or with a midrib only; ligule absent. Homosporous; sporangia at the base of scale- or leaf-like sporophylls, frequently in cones. Prothallus subterranean, mostly saprophytic and mycorrhizal.
