\pard\f0\fs28 Stems short, ascending and divided dichotomously into branches of equal length. Leaves and sporophylls similar, in alternating zones in the upper branches; sporangia reniform, pedunculate; spores foveolate-punctate. Prothallus holosaprophytic, subterranean, large and cylindrical.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 {\b 1. H. selago} (L.) Bernh. ex Schrank & C.F.P. Mart.,{\i  Hort. Monac}. 3 (1829) ({\i Lycopodium selago} L.). Stem 5-30 cm, erect. Leaves imbricate, in many rows on the stem, appressed or patent, linear to ovate-lanceolate, usually entire, often bearing in their axils bud-like gemmae.{\i  Europe southwards to N. Spain and N. Greece; mainly on mountains except in the north}. All except Bl Cr Gr Lu Rs(K, E) Sa Si Tu.
\par

